This paper deals with packet scheduling algorithms in computer networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses theoretical and empirical analysis of these algorithms, which could also fall under the sub-categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), information theory (cs.IT), control and systems engineering (cs.SY), and performance (cs.PF).
